title: Tomato Feta Pasta Salad
description:
This tomato feta pasta salad seems to get better every time I make it! ¬≠‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏èüî•üî• CLICK FOR RECIPE üî•üî•‚¨áÔ∏è‚¨áÔ∏è #tomatofetapasta #tomatofetapastasalad #tomatofeta

PRINT THE RECIPE ‚û°Ô∏è https://www.theslowroasteditalian.com/tomato-feta-pasta-salad/

Ingredients ‚¨áÔ∏è
1/2 pound rotini pasta
kosher salt
extra virgin olive oil
1 pound grape tomatoes, halved
3/4 cup kalamata olives, pitted and halved
1 pound feta cheese, medium-diced
6 sun-dried tomatoes in oil, drained and chopped

For the dressing
5 sun-dried tomatoes in oil, drained
2 tablespoons red wine vinegar
6 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil
1 clove garlic, diced
1 teaspoon kosher salt
3/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
1 cup freshly grated parmesan cheese
1 cup packed flat-leaf parsley, chopped

Instructions ‚¨áÔ∏è
Cook the pasta in a large pot of boiling salted water. Boil for 12 minutes, or according to the directions on the package. Drain well and allow to cool. 

Place the pasta in a bowl and add the tomatoes, olives, feta and chopped sun-dried tomatoes.

For the dressing, combine the sun-dried tomatoes, vinegar, olive oil, garlic, salt and pepper in a food processor until almost smooth.

Pour the dressing over the pasta, sprinkle with the Parmesan and parsley, and toss well.

Serve immediately or cover with plastic wrap, refrigerate and serve later.

title: Grinding my own matcha in Japan!
description:
I ground my own matcha in Japan! This was one of my favourite experiences from the trip and being a heavy matcha drinker myself, it was awesome getting to learn how to prepare my own bowl of ceremonial matcha in the capital of matcha - Uji, Japan. I highly recommend trying this out if you like drinking matcha! Also secretly debating if I should get a stone mill üò¨

For those asking, there are many tea factories and matcha shops in Uji that offer matcha workshops! We decided last minute to do it but everything was fully booked so they pointed us to the Chazuna community centre which offers a very good workshop taught by very nice instructors!

title: making a matcha latte at home üçµ
description:
matcha latte at home üçµ ~

Making myself a cup of matcha is one of the things I look forward to most in the morning. It‚Äôs almost peaceful, in a way - and I feel so energized after.

The most important ingredient is, of course, the matcha. You want to use the highest quality for drinking, which is ceremonial grade. It is pricy, but you‚Äôre going to save so much money compared to spending $8 each time at a cafe.

* the matcha I‚Äôm using is from @tenzotea ‚Äî you can use my code for a discount! JASMINE15
-- https://tenzotea.co/

For today's matcha I used soy milk with a splash of homemade maple syrup (the best kind). On most days though, I‚Äôll drink it the traditional way with just water and matcha. Experiment and see which flavor combinations you like best!

title: PH√î MAI MATCHA #food
$1 Matcha vs Starbucksüßã
Is this homemade MATCHA BOBA actually worth the effort?
description:
Is this homemade MATCHA BOBA actually worth the effort?

‚ú®Recipe: 
‚ú®Prepare the brown sugar boba pearls: In a small saucepan, combine the 1/3cup water and 1/3cup light brown sugar. Heat mixture over high heat until boiling. Reduce the heat to low and mix in 1/2cup of tapioca starch, stirring constantly for 6-8 seconds. Remove from heat and mix in another 1/2cup of tapioca starch until a dough just begins to form. 
Dump the dough out onto a work surface and knead until a smooth dough forms, about 1 minute or so. Working quickly, as the dough will dry up if it cools too much, divide the dough into four equal pieces and roll each piece into a long rod and then cut and form into little balls. 
‚ú®Place the boba pearls into a bowl with tapioca starch and toss to coat. Dump the boba into a fine-mesh sieve to shake off the excess tapioca starch. 
‚ú®To cook the boba pearls, heat a medium pot of water over medium-high heat until boiling. Add the pearls and boil for 30 minutes. Cut the heat and let the pearls rest in the water for 20-25 minutes or until translucent and chewy. 
‚ú®Make the Brown Sugar Syrup:  To a small saucepot, add 6 1/2 TBLS of water and 1 1/4cup light brown sugar and swirl to combine. Place over medium heat and cook until the sugar dissolves and the mixture starts to bubble. Increase the heat to medium-high and boil vigorously to reduce the liquid into a syrup. Drain the pearls through a fine-mesh strainer. Stir into the syrup mixture along with 1 tbls of blackstrap molasses. 
‚ú®To assemble with traditional milk tea, add 2cups of whole milk to a small saucepan over medium heat. Heat the milk until it reaches 162¬∞F (72¬∞C), stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and mix in 5 black tea bags. Let steep for 4-8 minutes, or until it reaches the desired strength of flavor. Refrigerate until completely cold. To a tall glass, spoon in as many boba pearls as desired and top with desired amount of syrup. Add in the ice cubes before pouring in the chilled milk tea and serve. 
‚ú®To assemble the matcha, I used a specific boba matcha powder. Heat 2 cups milk like above, and pour in the matcha according to package. Assemble the same way as above. Enjoy! üòâ

description:
The answer, if you ask me, is any plant milk you like BUT I would not recommend dairy milk, and I promise I‚Äôm not just saying that because I‚Äôm vegan.

When you mix matcha directly with milk, the casein protein in dairy milk binds to polyphenols in matcha, alters the bioavailability and blocks absorption of antioxidants. In short, you‚Äôre missing out on potential health benefits that matcha has to offer.

The good news is, this isn‚Äôt an issue with plant milk, so opt for something like oat, almond, soy or whatever else you‚Äôd like! It‚Äôs better for the planet anyway üôÇ

title: How to make matcha tea properly!
description:
This is how to prepare matcha correctly at home!

1. Sift 1-2 teaspoons of matcha to remove clumps.
2. Heat water to just below boiling.
3. Soak your bamboo whisk in warm water.
4. Mix a bit of hot water with the matcha.
5. Whisk vigorously in a "W" pattern until frothy.
6. Add more water for a thinner drink, if desired.
7. Sip immediately to enjoy it at its best.
Perfecting matcha takes practice, but it's well worth the effort!

title: Use Matcha Tea As Coffee Alternative ‚Äì Dr. Berg
description:

Are you looking for a reason to replace coffee with matcha tea? This video‚Äôs for you. 

0:00 Introduction: Matcha tea as a coffee replacement
0:30 Matcha tea benefits
1:17 Try it out!

In this video, I‚Äôm going to go over the many health benefits of matcha tea. Matcha tea is a super-concentrated green tea, made by taking the entire green tea leaf and grinding it into a fine powder.

Consuming one cup of matcha is the equivalent of consuming 10 cups of green tea, with only half the caffeine of a cup of black coffee. One serving of matcha contains around 31 mg of caffeine. Matcha green tea also contains the amino acid L-theanine which is very calming. 

Here are some matcha tea benefits: 
‚Ä¢No jittery feelings
‚Ä¢Feelings of calmness from L-theanine
‚Ä¢Provides more energy than coffee
‚Ä¢Improves mental clarity and endurance
‚Ä¢137x the phytonutrients as 1 cup of green tea
‚Ä¢Decreases inflammation 
‚Ä¢Supports the immune system

Oftentimes, when people quit coffee they experience headaches and other withdrawal symptoms. If you use matcha tea as a coffee replacement, you won‚Äôt experience any of these negative side effects.

title: How to make Chewy Matcha Mochi filled with cheese cream #recipe#mochi #matcha #cake#trending #shorts
description:
How to make Chewy Matcha Mochi filled with cheese cream #recipe#mochi #matcha #cake#trending #shortsviral 

Matcha Cheese Filling Mouchi Recipe below

Mochi Skin

Glutinous rice flour 100g
Cornstarch 30g
Granulated sugar 20g
Milk 170g
Butter 15g

Matcha Cheese Filling

Cream cheese 200g
Granulated sugar 30g
Matcha powder 8g
Heavy cream 150g

1„ÄÅMix glutinous rice flour, cornstarch, granulated sugar, and milk until well combined. Sift the mixture, cover with plastic wrap, poke a few small holes, and microwave on high for 3 minutes or steam on high for 25 minutes.

2„ÄÅWhile hot, add the butter and knead until smooth and elastic.

3„ÄÅMelt the cream cheese and stir until smooth. Add the granulated sugar and matcha powder, and mix well. Add the heavy cream and mix until combined. Divide the mixture into 6 portions, place them in plastic wrap, and freeze for one hour.

4„ÄÅSprinkle cooked flour on the mochi skin and roll it into a round sheet, not too thin. Place the frozen matcha cheese filling in the center, wrap it up, and trim off the excess dough.

5„ÄÅSprinkle with matcha powder and enjoy.

Thanks for watching!

description:

#homecafe #matchalatte #youneedtoknow 

Ube Cream Matcha Latte: A Bold Fusion with My New Matcha Ceremonia Kit
There‚Äôs nothing quite like the moment when you find your new favorite drink‚Äîespecially when it‚Äôs a colorful, delicious, and unique blend of flavors. Lately, I‚Äôve been obsessed with the Ube Cream Matcha Latte, a drink that combines the smooth earthiness of matcha with the rich, creamy taste of ube. What makes it even more special is creating it using my new matcha essential kit, which elevates the experience to a whole new level!

Today, I‚Äôm sharing the recipe for this dreamy Ube Cream Matcha Latte, and trust me, once you try it, you‚Äôll be hooked too.

What You'll Need:
Matcha (~2 tsps)
Milk (100ml)
Heavy Cream (50ml)
Ube Extract (1 tbsp, add sugar if you want it sweeter)
Ladyfinger (for garnish)
How to Make Ube Cream Matcha Latte
Step 1: Cold Whisked Matcha
The base of this latte starts with a beautifully whisked matcha. I use 2 teaspoons of matcha and whisk it with 100ml of cold milk using the tools from my matcha ceremonia kit. The bamboo whisk creates a perfectly smooth and frothy matcha blend that is absolutely essential for achieving the right texture and flavor.

Pro Tip: Whisk in a ‚ÄúW‚Äù motion to create an even froth. This technique, combined with the traditional whisk from the kit, ensures your matcha is well-blended and free of clumps.

Step 2: Ube Cream
Next comes the star of the drink‚Äîube cream. In a small bowl, whip 50ml of heavy cream with 1 tablespoon of ube extract. You can adjust the sweetness by adding sugar to taste, but I personally love the subtle sweetness of ube on its own. The result is a thick, luscious purple cream that‚Äôs full of rich flavor.

Step 3: Layering the Drink
Pour the cold whisked matcha into a glass, and then gently spoon the ube cream on top. The visual contrast between the deep green matcha and the vibrant purple ube cream is stunning‚Äîit‚Äôs a feast for the eyes as much as it is for the taste buds!

Step 4: Topping It Off
For an extra treat, I like to top my Ube Cream Matcha Latte with a ladyfinger. It adds a delightful crunch and makes the experience of drinking this latte feel even more indulgent.

Why the Matcha Ceremonia Kit is a Must-Have
Ever since I got my matcha essential kit, making matcha has become more than just preparing a drink‚Äîit‚Äôs a mindful ritual that I look forward to every day. The bamboo whisk is perfect for creating the right consistency, and the whole kit brings an authentic and calming vibe to the process. Using the traditional tools helps me connect with the rich history of matcha preparation while also making it easier to achieve that perfect froth.

Final Thoughts
The Ube Cream Matcha Latte is not just a treat for the taste buds‚Äîit‚Äôs a drink that‚Äôs as visually striking as it is flavorful. The earthy notes of matcha blend perfectly with the creamy, nutty flavor of ube, and when you add in the elegance of the ceremonia kit, making this latte feels like a creative, satisfying process.

If you‚Äôre looking for something new to try, give this recipe a go! And don‚Äôt forget, a matcha essential kit can make all the difference in creating the perfect drink, helping you bring both tradition and taste into every cup.

description:
Recipe‚§µÔ∏è Would you eat this?

Matcha Mochi Ice Cream

Ingredients:
1 cup glutinous rice flour, plus more for dusting
¬º cup granulated sugar
2 tsp matcha powder
‚Öî cup water
Green tea ice cream, for filling

Directions:
In a bowl, combine the rice flour, sugar, and matcha powder
Add in the water, then whisk until smooth
In a nonstick pan on medium/ low heat, cook the rice flour mixture until thickened, stirring constantly with a nonstick spatula
The mixture will become a dough, once that happens, fold it over itself a few times, then remove from the heat
Dust a glass bowl with a bit of rice flour, then add the mochi dough into it
Pound with a wooden pestle, folding it over itself occasionally, until you heat a popping sound
Dust a flat surface with rice flour and roll the dough out into a log around 1 ¬Ω inch
Divide into 8 pieces
Roll each piece into a ball, then flatten it
Place over a small bowl, letting the edges dangle over the sides
Place a small scoop of the green tea ice cream in the center, then bring the sides of the dough over it to completely close
Cut off any excess dough and add a bit of rice flour on top to make it less sticky
Place in the freezer so that the ice cream doesn‚Äôt melt while you repeat for the rest of the dough
Once ready to serve, dust with more matcha powder

Enjoy!!

title: Benefits of Matcha #shorts
description:
Benefits of Matcha #shorts

Dr. Janine shares the benefits of matcha.  She talks about how matcha is made from the buds and top three layers of young and shade-grown tea plants.  She explains that the active ingredients in matcha are caffeine, catechins, chlorophyll, and theanine.  Dr. Janine shares research looking at the benefits of matcha for weight loss.  She looks at a study that found matcha tea was higher in catechins than other types of tea.  She explains how the catechins in matcha can also help protect against heart disease, diabetes, and cancer.  Dr. Janine does suggest making your own matcha as store-bought lattes can contain sugar and other unfavorable ingredients.

Green tea extract ingestion, fat oxidation, and glucose tolerance in healthy humans - https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18326618/ 
Determination of catechins in matcha green tea by micellar electrokinetic chromatography - https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/14518774/

Making a Mango Sticky Rice Matcha Latte ü•≠üçµ #mango #matcha #matchalatte
description:
Making a matcha latte üçµ‚Ä¶but mango sticky rice flavored! Mango sticky rice ü•≠ is easily one of my favorite desserts and the combination of ripe mangoes and coconut cream pairs so well with matcha. Soo be sure to save this post if you need some summertime ‚òÄÔ∏è matcha inspiration! 

Ingredients
¬Ω mango (pureed) + agave (depending on preferred sweetness)

4g matcha powder (from @matchakari)
40ml hot water (preferably at 175F)
120ml milk of choice

2 tbsp of heavy cream
1 tbsp of coconut cream
1 tsp condensed milk
Pinch of salt

Sprinkle of black sesame seeds
Sprig of mint
Drizzle of condensed milk

Recipe
Puree half a mango in a food processor or blender. Add agave if mango is not sweet. Optional: save a few pieces of mango for garnish.
For the cream topping, blend together heavy cream, coconut cream, and pinch of salt. Set aside.
Prepare matcha by sifting matcha powder and whisking with hot water.
Layer in order: mango puree, ice, milk, matcha, cream.
Top with cubed mangoes, a drizzle of condensed milk, sprig of mint, and black sesame seeds
Mix and enjoy!

üí° Inspired by @loveemanda and @ispillice to make this unique drink!

WHY I QUIT COFFEE // MY HONEY MATCHA LATTE
description:
I had no idea my 1-month experiment swapping coffee for matcha would make me such a die hard matcha fan üòÜ When I started bringing awareness to my hormone health last year I took a long, hard look at what habits of mine weren't supporting healthy hormones and my morning double espresso latte started to set off alarm bells üö®

I realized that coffee made me experience jitters and anxiety that manifested both physically (restlessness, sweating, shakiness) and mentally (irritability, trouble concentrating). I had to come to terms with the reality that the relationship I had with my morning coffee was toxic - I loved it but it didn't love me back ü•≤ So I made the switch and this is what I experienced: 

- Weeks 1 and 2 I CRAVED coffee. Matcha just didn't hit the same or give me that BURST of "let's goooo" energy that I had become dependent on to will myself into conquering the day
- Week 3 I started to adapt to the change and didn't think about coffee. I also got used to the slow-release caffeine in matcha that provides a more gradual increase in energy 
- Week 4 I had a coffee while traveling and it tasted BAD. I did not enjoy it at all, and not in a "this is bad coffee" way but in a "my tastebuds have reset and I don't like this" way 
- After that there was no looking back! My coffee cravings were gone, I'd fully come to appreciate the taste, ritual, and feeling of matcha, and I no longer even liked coffee. 

I actually had a coffee a month ago when the coffee shop we frequent was out of matcha and all those old symptoms of shakiness, trouble focusing, and anxiety rushed back üòµ‚Äçüí´ thus proving to me why I made the switch!

HONEY MATCHA LATTE‚ú® 
1 tsp matcha powder (I used @piquelife - discount in my bio)
3 oz cold water 
1/2 - 1 tsp honey (I like @manukora manuka honey)
1/3 cup creamy vanilla cashew milk (recipe in my January reels)

To make your latte:
Add the water to a small glass or bowl 
Spoon the matcha powder through a fish mesh sieve to break up any clumps 
Whisk in a front to back motion until slightly frothy on top 
Add the honey and whisk again 
Add ice to your serving glass 
Pour in the milk and top with your honey matcha mixture 
ENJOY!

Follow for more simple, healthy recipes! 
.

description:
My dream is to open an Asian caf√©, and I‚Äôm building a menu one drink at a time with you here! This Mango Matcha recipe is sweet, earthy, and absolutely perfect for summer. 

1 ripe mango 
2 tbsps honey 
1.5 tsps matcha powder 
2 Tbsps hot water 
1/2 cup milk of choice 
Lots of ice 

Process: 

- Chop the mango super fine, add honey and continue chopping 
- Pass the matcha powder through a sieve and whisk with a matcha bamboo whisk that has been soaked in water 
- Whisk until nice and frothy 
- To assemble, start with the mango at the base, Top up with ice, pour over the milk and the matcha 
- Stir and enjoy chilled!

description:
Matcha milk jellyüçµüíö

Recipe:
1. Bloom 1.25 tsp of gelatin powder in 1 tbsp of cold water
2. Whisk 2 tsp matcha powder with a little bit of hot water to make a paste
3. Heat 1 cup milk and add in 1 tbsp sugar 
4. Add gelatin to hot milk and mix until fully dissolved
5. Mix in matcha paste and pour into container
6. Let set for at least 4 hours
7. Cut into rectangular shapes and enjoy!

This Dubai Chocolate Bar SNAPS!

‚ú®Recipe:
1 cup pistachio paste
1 to 1 ¬Ω cup shredded phyllo dough, cut into small pieces
vegetable oil
2 to 3 cups milk chocolate, melted
¬º cup white chocolate, melted
1 cup flour 
¬Ω cup corn starch
¬º tsp salt
2 tbsp oil
1 ¬Ω cup water

1. In a mold, drizzle white chocolate over and heat baking chocolate (not too hot so it looses it‚Äôs temper) as the first layer. Place in the fridge to let that layer set 

Making the Shredded Phyllo Dough (homemade because everywhere is sold out):
1. In a bowl add the flour, cornstarch, salt, oil & water together, whisk until completely smooth. 
2. Strain out all the lumps from the batter and fill a squeeze tube fitted with a super tiny nozzle.
3. Squeeze a small amount of batter out in thin strands until fried. Place aside when they start to pull up.

2. In a pan add the shredded phyllo dough with a small amount of frying oil. Fry until golden brown. Add the pistachio paste and mix together. 
3. Add another layer of melted tempered chocolate overtop of the mold. Set in the fridge until completely harden
4. Pop out of the mold, listen to that ASMR crack and enjoy üòâ

Is the VIRAL DUBAI CHOCOLATE MILKSHAKE worth the hype?
description:
Is the VIRAL DUBAI CHOCOLATE MILKSHAKE worth the hype?

‚ú®Recipe:
Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 2-3 cups vanilla ice cream
‚Ä¢ 1 ¬Ω cups knafeh (shredded phyllo dough)
‚Ä¢ 8 oz jar pistachio spread
‚Ä¢ 8 oz semi-sweet baking chocolate
‚Ä¢ Neutral oil, for frying

Directions:
1. Melt the baking chocolate over low heat until smooth. Pour the melted chocolate into a 16 oz flexible plastic cup and rotate to coat the inside.
2. Freeze the cup for 20‚Äì30 minutes, or until the chocolate is fully set.
3. In a blender, combine the vanilla ice cream, pistachio spread, and fried knafeh. Blend until smooth and creamy.
4. Pour the milkshake into your chocolate-coated cup and top with extra knafeh, pistachio drizzle, or whipped cream if you‚Äôre feeling fancy.
5. Serve immediately and enjoy this ultra-luxe, TikTok-worthy shake! üíö‚ú®

‚ú®Recipe:
Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 1 (16 oz) cup
‚Ä¢ Strawberries, sliced
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp unsalted butter
‚Ä¢ Kataifi, shredded
‚Ä¢ Pistachio spread
‚Ä¢ Semi-sweet bakers chocolate

Directions:
1. In a medium pan on medium heat, add the butter kataifi and stir until kataifi starts browning. Remove from heat and mix in the pistachio spread.
2. Melt the chocolate, adding a little to the bottom of your cup. Place some sliced strawberries around the edges of the cup, then start layering alternate layers of the pistachio mixture, strawberries, and chocolate.
3. Top with a few more strawberries, serve immediately, and enjoy! üòä

Can these PISTACHIO BROWNIES beat out the Dubai chocolate bar? #summervibes
description:
Can these PISTACHIO BROWNIES beat out the Dubai chocolate bar? #summervibes

‚ú®recipe: 
16 oz Chocolate
1 ¬Ω cup (3 sticks) Unsalted Butter
2 ¬Ω cup Sugar
2 ¬Ω cup Flour
¬Ω cup Cocoa Powder
2 tsp Salt
4 Eggs
4 tsp Vanilla Extract

Directions:
1. Chop chocolate into bite sized pieces. In a saucepan on medium heat, melt butter and add in chocolate. Stir until completely melted and combined.
2. In a separate bowl, mix sugar, cocoa powder, and salt. Once mixed, add eggs, and vanilla. Whisk until combined and rolling off whisk in ribbons.
3. Sift in flour and using a spatula, fold into batter. Add in melted chocolate/butter and fold until smooth. Add remaining chocolate chunks.
4. Place batter into a greased 9x13 glass pan lined with parchment paper. Dollop pistachio butter and swirl into batter using a knife. Top with finely chopped pistachio nuts and bake at 325¬∞F for 45 minutes.
5. Let cool slightly outside of oven until you can handle the pan with your bare hands. Place into fridge and let cool for 1 hour.
6. Cut into 1 ¬Ω inch squares, serve and enjoy! üòâ

Mezclar con la crema de pistacho: Una vez que los fideos est√©n listos, mezcla con la crema de pistacho hasta obtener una masa homog√©nea. Reserva.

Colorear el chocolate (opcional): Si deseas a√±adir l√≠neas de colores al exterior, divide el chocolate derretido en porciones y a√±ade unas gotas de colorante alimentario a cada una. Mezcla bien hasta obtener los colores deseados.

A√±adir el relleno: Coloca la mezcla de crema de pistacho y fideos sobre la capa de chocolate, distribuy√©ndola uniformemente.
Cubrir con m√°s chocolate: Vierte otra capa de chocolate derretido sobre el relleno, asegur√°ndote de cubrirlo completamente.
A√±adir las l√≠neas de colores: Si has preparado chocolate de diferentes colores, utiliza una cuchara o una manga pastelera para a√±adir l√≠neas decorativas sobre la capa superior de chocolate. Puedes crear patrones seg√∫n tu preferencia.
Enfriar y desmoldar:

description:
The Sugar Spike Show goes to Dubai! I‚Äôll be testing Middle Eastern classics like hummus, shawarma, and kunafa to see which dishes spike my sugar a lot and which keep it steady. 
.
Dubai Series Schedule:
1. Chicken Junglee Sandwich: +40mg
2. Hummus Pita: +23mg
3. Chicken Shawarma (N-Veg) +26MG
4. Falafel Shawarma (Veg) +27mg
5. Dates *TODAY*
6. Kunafa Chocolate
7. Frozen Yogurt
8. Chicken Haleem
9. Mutton Nihari & Naan
10. Paneer Tikka Sandwich
11. Quick Series Summary
12. Blooper Video
.
Disclaimer: I‚Äôm not a diabetic. Results are different for each person, especially for diabetics & can change from recipe to recipe. My own results vary a little day to day. Ideally, each person should tests on themselves. Glycemic load, calories, quality & quantity of food, all of these matter. Finally, I am not a doctor & this is not medical advice. 
.
How to see my results: Best is to get an idea of which foods spike more and which ones spike less, and develop an intuition based on ingredients. Don‚Äôt focus on absolute numbers. 
.
Why I‚Äôm doing this if I‚Äôm not a diabetic: I‚Äôve noticed that having steady glucose levels makes me feel good & I get lesser food cravings. Plus, prevention is the best medicine. Research today shows that high blood sugar variability over time can lead to diabetes, heart disease & obesity. Please see the work of Dr. Rob Lustig, Dr. Casey Means, Dr. Michael Snyder & Jessie Inchausp√©.
.
My personal aim:
1. Blood sugar increase after eating = 30-40mg/dl or lower
2. Return to baseline = Within 3 hours 
3. Range = Be within 70-120mg/dl for¬†80%¬†of¬†the¬†day

title: High protein dark chocolate pistachio Dubai cheesecake
description:
High Protein Dubai Chocolate Pistachio Cheesecake

It‚Äôs finally HERE! The simple, healthy version of the viral Dubai cheesecake that we‚Äôve all been waiting for! 

I absolutely LOVE the combo of chocolate and pistachios, they make this cheesecake feel completely INDULGENT! So rich, so delicious, trust me you want to try this one! 

Ingredients

Cake
1 cup cottage cheese
1 cup Greek yogurt 
2 eggs  
1/2 cup cocoa powder 
1/2 cup maple syrup or honey
1/4 cup oat or almond flour 
1 tsp vanilla

Toppings
3/4 cup pistachios, chopped
1/2 cup cottage cheese 
2 tbsp maple syrup or honey

Instructions
Blend ingredients in a blender until smooth. 

Pour into a parchment lined 6‚Äù round baking dish. Spoon over 1/4 cup chopped pistachios and use a spoon to swirl through the batter. 

Bake at 325F for 40-45 minutes. The edges should feel set but the centre should still have a bit of jiggle when you move the dish. 

Cool in the fridge for a minimum of 8 hours. Overnight is best. 

While cooling, make the topping. Blend 1/4 cup pistachios with 1/2 cup cottage cheese and 2 tbsp maple syrup. Spread over the cooled cheesecake and top with remaining chopped pistachios. 

Enjoy!

‚ú®Recipe: 
1 cup Flour

¬Ω cup Cocoa Powder

2 tsp Vanilla

Directions:
1. In a medium bowl, melt and mix your butter with half (6oz) of your chocolate and combine well with a whisk or hand mixer.

6. Let rest for until completely cool on counter, or refrigerate, then cut into squares, serve and enjoy üòä

title: Can these AIR FRYER CHURROS beat out the originals?
description:
Can these AIR FRYER CHURROS beat out the originals?

‚ú®Recipe:
Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 1 cup water
‚Ä¢ ¬º cup unsalted butter, cubed
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp granulated sugar
‚Ä¢ ¬º tsp salt
‚Ä¢ 1 cup all-purpose flour
‚Ä¢ 2 large eggs
‚Ä¢ ¬Ω tsp vanilla extract
‚Ä¢ Vegetable oil spray (for air frying)
For the Cinnamon Sugar Coating:
‚Ä¢ ¬Ω cup granulated sugar
‚Ä¢ ¬æ tsp ground cinnamon

Directions:
1. In a shallow dish, whisk together the sugar and cinnamon. Set aside.
2. In a medium saucepan over medium-high heat, bring the water, butter, sugar, and salt to a boil. Reduce heat to low and stir in the flour, mixing continuously until a smooth dough forms, about 1‚Äì2 minutes. Transfer to a mixing bowl and let cool for 5 minutes.
3. Add the vanilla extract and egg to the dough. Using an electric mixer, blend until fully combined and smooth. (It may look like it's separating at first‚Äîkeep mixing, and it will come together!).
4. Transfer the dough to a piping bag fitted with a small star tip (no larger than ¬Ω inch). Pipe 4-inch lengths onto a parchment-lined tray, using scissors to cut the ends cleanly.
5. Lightly coat the air fryer basket with oil spray. Arrange the churros in a single layer, ensuring they aren‚Äôt touching. Air fry at 375¬∞F for 10‚Äì12 minutes or until golden brown and crisp.
9. While warm, toss the churros in the cinnamon-sugar mixture until fully coated. Serve immediately with chocolate ganache or warmed nutella for dipping, and enjoy!üòä

title: Are AIR FRYER POTATO CHIPS worth the hype?!
description:
Are AIR FRYER POTATO CHIPS worth the hype?!

‚ú®Recipe:
Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 1 to 3 Yukon Gold potatoes
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp olive oil
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp salt
‚Ä¢ Optional: Extra seasoning of choice (like paprika, garlic powder, or ranch seasoning)

Directions:
1. Using a mandolin (or a sharp knife), slice the potatoes very thinly‚Äîcutting at a slight angle for larger chips if you like.
2. Soak the potato slices in an ice water bath for 10 minutes to help remove excess starch. Drain and repeat once more.
3. After the second soak, drain the potatoes and pat them completely dry with paper towels.
4. Toss the slices in a bowl with olive oil and salt, making sure every chip is lightly coated.
5. Arrange the potato slices in a single layer inside the air fryer basket (you‚Äôll need to cook them in batches).
6. Air fry at 350¬∞F for 15‚Äì20 minutes, flipping the chips every 5 minutes. Remove chips as they turn golden and crispy, since some may cook faster than others.
7. Let cool slightly, sprinkle with your favorite seasonings if desired, and enjoy!

title: How to make poori using airfryer, watch the full recipe on my channel.
description:
Who says pooris need oil? ‚ú®
These air fryer pooris are light, fluffy, and guilt-free!
Just flour, curd, and a few minutes in the fryer ‚Äî puffed magic on your plate üíõ
Perfect for a healthy twist on a classic favorite

Give it try and let me know what you think. Come on yaüíï

Head to my YouTube channel for the full recipe. 

Ingredients:
* 1 cup whole wheat flour
* ¬º tsp salt (or as needed)
* 1¬Ω tbsp curd
* Water (as needed)

Steps:
1. In a bowl, mix flour, salt, and curd. Add little water at a time and knead into a firm dough.
2. Cover and rest the dough for 15 minutes.
3. Divide into small balls and roll them into pooris (not too thin).
4. Preheat the air fryer at 190¬∞C.
5. Place the pooris inside and air fry for 6 minutes or until puffed and golden.
üëâ Soft, crispy pooris ready without oil!

title: Don't buy an airfryer #shorts
description:
Don't buy an airfryer #shorts

 Safety Tip for Air Fryer Users: Why You Should Use a Mesh Basket

Air fryers have changed the way we prepare meals, but safety is still a top priority. One important accessory to consider is a stainless steel mesh basket.

#### Why Use a Mesh Basket?

Air fryers cook by circulating hot air around the food, but lighter items like fries, chips, or certain vegetables can be easily lifted by this airflow. This can result in:

- **Clogged Heating Elements:** Tiny food particles can become trapped in the heating elements, potentially damaging the appliance.
- **Fire Risk:** In extreme cases, a buildup of debris could create a fire hazard.

#### Benefits of a Mesh Basket:

A mesh basket can help mitigate these issues by:

- **Containing Food:** It keeps your food in place, preventing it from being blown around the air fryer.
- **Promoting Even Cooking:** The basket allows for better heat circulation, ensuring that your food cooks uniformly.
- **Facilitating Easy Cleaning:** Mesh baskets are typically easy to clean, making them a practical addition to your kitchen.

Investing in a stainless steel mesh basket lets you take full advantage of air frying while enhancing safety.

title: AIR FRYER CHICKEN DRUMSTICKS RECIPE | GRILLED CHICKEN LEGS IN AIR FRYER
description:
Air Fryer Chicken Drumsticks Recipe | Grilled Chicken Legs In Air Fryer | Air Fryer Chicken | Chicken Drumsticks Recipe | Air Fryer Chicken Legs | Air Fryer Grilled Chicken | Air Fryer Tandoori Chicken

Ingredients for Air Fryer Chicken Drumsticks:

(Tsp- Teaspoon; Tbsp- Tablespoon )

- Chicken Drumsticks (about 6)- 500 gms 

For Marination:
- Whisked Curd/Yogurt- 3 tbsp
- Ginger Garlic paste- 1 tsp
- Turmeric Powder- 1/4 tsp
- Red Chilli Powder- 1 tsp
- Coriander Powder- 1 tsp
- Kashmiri Chilli Powder- 1.5 tsp
- Garam Masala Powder- 1/2 tsp
- Salt- 1 tsp
- Lemon juice - 1 tsp
- Refined Oil - 2 tbsp

Other Ingredients:
- Melted Butter for basting-1-2 tbsp

Preparation:

- Wash and pat dry the chicken drumsticks. Make two cuts on each of the drumsticks.
- Whisk the curd/yogurt and add all the other ingredients to make the mix. Whisk it well until smooth
- Add all the drumsticks and mix well to coat the drumsticks well with the marinade.
- Cover and set aside on room temperature for around 90 mins.

Process :

- Take out the basket from the Air fryer and brush it with 1 tsp oil.
- Now place the marinated chicken drumsticks at an angle in the basket as shown in the video to fit all the pieces. 
- Put the basket back into the Air fryer and set temperature at 180¬∞C and time at 20 mins.
- Let it cook for 10 mins and then press Pause.
- Remove the basket and brush the pieces with melted butter. Put the basket back into the air fryer.
- If your air fryer requires, you can flip the drumsticks at this point and brush with melted butter. 
- Put the basket back and cook for another 10 minutes at 180¬∞C
- Remove and check if the chicken is cooked. Otherwise you may cook for 2-3 mins more at 180¬∞C
- Remove and serve hot as a starter.

title: AIR FRYER CHICKEN TIKKA | RESTAURANT STYLE CHICKEN TIKKA IN AIR FRYER
description:
Air Fryer Chicken Tikka | Restaurant Style Chicken Tikka in Air Fryer | Air Fryer Chicken | Chicken Tikka | Tandoori Chicken Tikka in Air Fryer | Chicken Tikka Kabab | How to Make Chicken Tikka

Ingredients for Air Fryer Chicken Tikka:

(Tsp - teaspoon; Tbsp - tablespoon)

- Boneless Chicken - 500 gms (cut into 2‚Äù tikka pieces)

Marinade:
- Hung Curd- 5 tbsp
- Turmeric Powder- a pinch (1/8 tsp)
- Kashmiri Chilli Powder- 5 tsp
- Cumin Powder- 1/2 tsp
- Garam Masala Powder- 1/2 tsp
- Mace Powder(Javitri Powder)- 1/2 tsp
- Kasuri Methi(Fenugreek Leaves), dry roasted & powdered- 1/2 tsp
- Salt- 1 tsp & a pinch
- Lemon Juice-2 tsp
- Ginger Garlic Paste- 1 tbsp
- Red Food colour- a pinch
- Cooking Oil- 3 tbsp

Other Ingredients:
- Butter, for basting(melted) - 1 tbsp

Preparation:
- To prepare the hung curd, strain the water from the curd or plain yogurt using a strainer or cloth to have a thick curd without any water. This may take 1.5 to 2 hrs, so plan accordingly.
- You can use chicken tikka pieces or alternatively cut boneless chicken fillets into tikkas. 
- Wash and pat dry the boneless chicken fillets. Cut into 2‚Äù tikka shapes.
- For the marinade, add all the ingredients in a bowl ,whisk everything together and then add the marinated chicken pieces 
- Set aside to marinate for 3-4 hours in the refrigerator. Take out the marinated chicken from the refrigerator after 3.5 hrs & keep it in room temperature for half an hour before skewering & placing in the Airfryer. 
- Soak the wooden skewers in a glass bowl in water for minimum 30 mins.

Process:

- Skewer the marinated chicken tikkas on a skewer 4 at a time.
- Take out the basket from the Air fryer and brush it with oil
- Place the skewers side by side on the basket and keep it back in the Air fryer
- Choose the mode Chicken (default temperature 180) and timing 20 mins.
- Please pause half way and brush the kebabs with melted butter.
- Close the basket and air fry for another 10 mins.
- Remove and serve hot

title: THE JUCIEST AIR FRYER CHICKEN BREAST
description:
Visit dliciouslyinspired.com to find the full printable recipe!
Shop this video - https://amzn.to/3Pnh3eT

Ingredients 
2 large chicken breasts, cut to make four equal width thinner pieces
Avocado oil spray 
1  tb salt, I use Celtic salt
1 tsp pepper
1 tsp smoked paprika 
1/2 tsp garlic powder, onion powder, dried parsley flakes

Instructions
First, make the spice rub by combing all the spices in a small bowl, mix to combine and set aside. Then, you want to make sure you preheat the air fryer for at least 5 minutes prior to cooking so it is nice, hot, and ready to go. I simply just turn on my air fryer on 390F or 198C for 5 minutes. Once you cut the chicken breast into thinner pieces, Lay it onto a cutting board, to both sides of the chicken add some avocado oil spray, rub it in, and then sprinkle on the spice rub, spread it all on the chicken with your fingers. Depending on the size of your air fryer you may need to do this in batches, I do two chicken breast slices at a time. Lay chicken in the preheated air fryer and cook on 390F for 4 minutes. Then flip the chicken over and cook and additional 3-4min. Make sure internal temp is at least 155F but preferably not more, chicken will continue to rise in temp one removed from the air fryer and will reach 165F. Rest for a few minutes slice and enjoy!

1. Preheat air fryer to 400¬∞F.

Using steel in airfryer? #shortsfeed
description:
Using steel in airfryer? #shortsfeed 
**Why Stainless Steel Utensils are Best for Air Fryers**

While air fryers are designed with non-stick coatings, using stainless steel utensils can provide several advantages:

* **Durability:** Stainless steel is a durable material that can withstand high temperatures and frequent use, ensuring longevity.
* **Safety:** Unlike non-stick coatings, stainless steel does not release harmful chemicals when heated to high temperatures. This is particularly important for air fryers, which often operate at high temperatures.
* **Easy Cleaning:** Stainless steel utensils are easy to clean and maintain, preventing the buildup of food particles and bacteria.

By opting for stainless steel utensils, you can enhance the safety and longevity of your air fryer while enjoying healthier and more flavorful meals.

description:

¬º teaspoon salt

Airfryer Pulav recipe
description:
Easy Air Fryer Pulao with the TurboBlaze! üçö‚ú® 

Learn how to easily make delicious and fragrant pulao using the Cosori TurboBlaze Air Fryer. This powerful appliance makes cooking your favorite dishes quicker and easier than ever. With its advanced technology and versatile settings, the TurboBlaze guarantees perfectly cooked rice and tender vegetables every time.

Rinse the basmati rice under cold water until the water runs clear. 
Soak the rice in 2 cups of water for about 20 minutes. 
Prepare the Veggies:
2.     

In a large mixing bowl, combine mixed vegetables, ginger garlic paste, green chilies with salt, turmeric powder, garam masala, cumin-coriander powder, and 1 tablespoon of oil or ghee. Also add in all the whole spices. Mix well to ensure the veggies are evenly coated with the spices.
Air Fry the Veggies:
3.     

Preheat your Cosori Turbo Blaze Air Fryer to 370¬∞F (190¬∞C).
Place the seasoned vegetables in the air fryer basket and air fry for 5 minutes. Shake the basket halfway through to ensure even cooking.
Cook the Rice with Veggies:
4.     

Add the soaked rice along with water to the air-fried vegetables in a bowl. Also, add the chopped tomatoes and adjust salt.
Cook in the Air Fryer:
5.     

Cover the bowl with aluminum foil to trap the steam and place it in the air fryer basket.
Cook at 370¬∞F (190¬∞C) for a total of 30 minutes, stirring once halfway through at the 15-minute mark to ensure even cooking.
Finish and Serve:
6.     

Once the cooking time is complete, remove the bowl from the air fryer and let it rest for a few minutes. Carefully remove the foil and fluff the rice with a fork.
Garnish with fresh coriander leaves.
Serve hot with yogurt raita

description:
Thinking about buying an air fryer? Wondering if it‚Äôs a healthy option or just another marketing gimmick? This video breaks down the facts about air frying vs deep frying and reveals what you need to know to cook healthier meals.

Learn why deep frying increases harmful compounds like HCAs, PAHs, COPs, and PFAs that raise cancer risk, while air frying uses lower temperatures and less oil, reducing acrylamide formation.

But air fryer health depends on how you use it! Follow these 5 tips for healthier air frying:

- Pre-soak potatoes and similar veggies for 10 minutes before cooking.
- Avoid very high temperatures.
- Keep cooking durations short.
- Clean your air fryer regularly.
- Choose healthier oils for cooking.

Don‚Äôt miss out on these simple yet effective tips to enjoy guilt-free, delicious air-fried food!

title: AIR FRYER GRILLED FISH | AIR FRIED GRILLED FISH RECIPE | GRILLED FISH RECIPE
description:
Air Fryer Grilled Fish | Air Fried Grilled Fish | Air Fryer Grilled Fish Recipe | How To Make Grilled Fish In Air Fryer | Grilled Fish Fillet In Air Fryer | Air Fryer Fish | Grilled Fish | Grilled Fish Fillets | Grilled Fish Recipe

Ingredients for Air Fryer Grilled Fish:

- Boneless fish fillets - 350 gms (Basa, Cod, Haddock,Sole or Catfish)

Marinade: 
- Cayenne pepper -1/2 tsp
- Black Pepper powder-1/2 tsp
- Garlic Powder-1/2 tsp
- Paprika-1/2 tsp
- Salt- 1/2 tsp
- Lemon juice- 1.5 tsp
- Oil-1.5 tbsp

Other Ingredients: 
- Oil spray - 
- Fine chopped parsley, for garnish- 1 tsp

Preparation:
- Cut the boneless fish fillets into required shape and pat dry.
- Now add all the ingredients for the marinade in a small bowl and mix it well. Apply the marinade on both sides of the fish fillets. Should coat the fish fillets completely. Set aside to marinate for 30 mins.

Process:

- Spray the air fryer basket with oil and then place the fish fillets side by side. 
- Make sure the fillets are completely coated with the marinade. 
- Now air fry on 180 for around 15 mins. 
- No need to flip the fish fillets. However you can flip the pieces if you want after 10 mins. 
- Lastly garnish with finely chopped parsley leaves for added flavor. 
- Serve hot with salad or saut√©ed vegetables on the side and maybe Tartar sauce.

title: The BEST CRISPY Air Fryer Chicken Thighs Recipe
description:
Get ready to make the crispiest, juiciest, and most satisfying chicken thighs you‚Äôve ever made! These air fryer chicken thighs are seasoned with a flavorful spice blend and then air fried until ultra crispy on the outside while remaining juicy on the inside. This will surely become one your favorite air fryer recipes!

Print recipe for free here ‚û°Ô∏è https://munchygoddess.com/air-fryer-chicken-thighs/

Ingredients:
5 chicken thighs bone-in, skin on (2 pounds)
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 teaspoon ground mustard seed
1 teaspoon smoked paprika
1 teaspoon onion powder
¬Ω teaspoon salt
¬Ω teaspoon ground black pepper
1 teaspoon garlic powder

Recipe Instructions:
1. Pat the chicken skin completely dry with a paper towel. Set aside.
2. To a large bowl, add the olive oil, ground mustard seed, smoked paprika, onion powder, salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Stir until well blended.
3. Add the chicken thighs to the bowl and toss until well coated.
4. Preheat the air fryer to 380 degrees Fahrenheit.
5. Once the air fryer is ready, add the chicken thighs to the air fryer skin-side down, and cook for 12 minutes.
6. After 12 minutes, open up the air fryer and flip the chicken. Return the chicken to the air fryer and cook for an additional 12 minutes or until the chicken reaches an internal temperature of 165 degrees Fahrenheit as measured by a food thermometer.
7. Once done, remove the chicken from the air fryer, let cool, and then enjoy!

title: Air Fryer Cookies | FeelGoodFoodie
description:
Did you know you can air fry cookies? I love this method for baking cookies in the summertime so I don‚Äôt have to turn on my oven. Plus it‚Äôs great for ‚Äúmeal prepping‚Äù because you can prep a big batch of cookies and just air fry as many as you need!
INGREDIENTS
¬Ω cup unsalted butter 1 stick, room temperature
¬Ω cup packed light brown sugar packed
¬º cup granulated sugar
1 large egg
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 ¬Ω cups all-purpose flour
¬Ω teaspoon baking powder
¬Ω teaspoon baking soda
¬º teaspoon salt
1 ¬º cup chocolate chips
INSTRUCTIONS
In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, combine the butter and sugars. Mix at medium speed for 2 to 3 minutes, or until light and fluffy. Add the egg and vanilla extract and mix until incorporated.
In a separate bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the butter mixture and mix until just combined.
Fold in the chocolate chips using a spatula or wooden spoon.
Using a medium spring-loaded cookie scoop, level, and roll about 1.5 tablespoons of the cookie dough and place them on one of the prepared baking sheets. You should get about 24 cookies. Cover and place in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour or overnight.
When ready to bake, line the air fryer with parchment paper and preheat to 325¬∞F. 
Place the cookie dough balls about 1 inch apart in the basket, leaving room for them to spread. If using parchment paper, you can slightly flatten the dough balls to help weigh it down and prevent it from flapping around. Bake for 7 minutes or until the edges are lightly golden.

title: super quick air fryer shrimp recipeüòä #lunch #airfryer #shrimp #easyrecipe #lunchideas #dinner
description:
Easy and Quick Air Fryer Shrimp:
- Put frozen shrimp in bowl and defrost them in the sink under running water. 
- Then pat dry and transfer to another bowl. 
- Drizzle in olive oil or avocado oil. 
- Add seasonings to taste: smoked paprika, fajita seasoning, and black pepper. 
- Mix and place into air fryer basket (don‚Äôt layer or overlap). 
- Air fry 3 minutes on 400F. Mix, and air fry another 3 minutes on 400F. (Make sure internal temp is 145F)
- That‚Äôs it! Enjoy with cocktail sauce or seafood butter sauce. 

Seafood Butter Sauce:
- 3 sticks butter, melted in saucepan on medium heat 
- Once butter has melted, add in:
- 1/2 dill bunch diced
- Several garlic cloves, minced
- Juice of 1 lemon 
- Salt to taste 
*Adjust these proportions to your liking. 
** Garlic sometimes turns green when cooking, that‚Äôs normal.

We gaan friet of patat maken met de Philips Airfryer Avance XL. Ik krijg regelmatig de vraag hoe je friet of patat moet airfryen en ik laat je zien hoe ik dat altijd doe.

700 gram verse friet uit koelschap (Hoogvliet)
22 minuten
180 graden (eerst voorverwarmen)

title: airfryer episode 41: baking cake in air fryer #shortsfeed
description:
airfryer episode 41: baking cake in air fryer #shortsfeed 

**Baking Cakes in an Air Fryer: A Professional Guide**

An air fryer isn't just for fries and snacks‚Äîit functions like a compact convection oven, making it ideal for baking cakes, cookies, and even bread. Its ability to circulate hot air evenly ensures consistent results in a fraction of the time a traditional oven might take.

When using an air fryer for baking, **preheating is essential**. Just like with standard ovens, preheating ensures that the batter is exposed to a stable temperature from the start, helping it rise properly and bake evenly.

For cakes, a temperature range of **160¬∞C to 180¬∞C** is generally ideal. However, baking at **160¬∞C** is often preferable, as it allows the cake to cook slowly and evenly. This lower temperature reduces the risk of the top browning or burning before the center is fully baked‚Äîespecially important in smaller air fryer chambers, where heat is more concentrated.

Key tips for successful air fryer cake baking:

* **Use a compatible cake tin** that fits comfortably inside the air fryer basket.
* **Line the tin** with parchment paper or grease it well to prevent sticking. 
* **Avoid overfilling** the tin; air fryer cakes rise just like oven-baked ones.
* **Check for doneness** using a toothpick‚Äîinsert it into the center; it should come out clean.

With the right temperature and timing, your air fryer can deliver soft, moist cakes with golden, perfectly set tops.

INGREDIENTI:
350 g fettine di pollo
70 g prosciutto cotto

Farciscile con il prosciutto cotto e la provola, quindi arrotola e taglia formando dei rotolini. Disponibili in teglia, aggiungi il resto del parmigiano (10 g) e un filo di olio EVO. Cuoci in friggitrice ad aria a 190¬∞C per 10-12 minuti. Oppure cuoci in forno a 200¬∞C per circa 25 minuti. Servi e‚Ä¶gusta!
